public static String replaceTable(String sql, String tableName) {
    if (org.springframework.util.CollectionUtils.isEmpty(tableName)) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Table name cannot be empty");
    }

    String[] words = sql.split("\\s+");
    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
    boolean tableNameFound = false;

    for (String word : words) {
        if (word.equalsIgnoreCase("from") || word.equalsIgnoreCase("join") || word.equalsIgnoreCase("update")) {
            tableNameFound = true;
            sb.append(tableName);
        } else if (tableNameFound) {
            tableNameFound = false;
            sb.append(word);
        } else {
            sb.append(word);
        }
        sb.append(" ");
    }

    return sb.toString().trim();
}
```

### Explanation:
This method works by splitting the SQL query into words. It then iterates over these words. If it encounters a word that is "from", "join", or "update", it knows that the next word is the table name, so it appends the provided table name instead. If it encounters a word that is not "from", "join", or "update" after having found a table name, it knows that the next word is not the table name, so it appends the word as is. The method returns the modified SQL query as a string.

